        "title": "Salinity",
        "excerpt":"In the Netherhlands we used a soil penetrometer for determining what?   which can be a simple two-probe device or a more complex four-electrode probe, passes an electrical current through the soil, and the resistance is measured   Short method description   Two or more electrodes are inserted into the soil to a specific depth. A voltage is applied across the electrodes. The resistance or conductivity of the soil to the current is measured. This measurement of electrical conductivity (EC) is used to estimate the total dissolved salts, which is a measure of soil salinity.   Scientific reports   Data access   Resources   Howebrew   RVM   Asdf   chruby   Frum   blog on installing Ruby on MacOS   ","categories": [],
